iced"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"320 g risotto rice (e.g. carnaroli, Arborio), 10-15 minutes cooking time (see tip)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"40 g dry white wine"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"740 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g lemon juice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 vegetable stock cube (for 0.5 l), crumbled"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ tsp fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 lemons, finely grated zest only"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp ground black pepper"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","3206 kJ \/ 763 kcal","25 g","62 g","45 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["The recipe uses ready-made puff pastry for convenience, but you can easily make your own quick puff in your Thermomix. Find the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","Double cream with <b>48% fat<b> or whipping cream with <b>35% fat<b> are both suitable for this recipe.","If time allows, return the salmon in puff pastry to the fridge for <b>30 minutes<b> before baking. This will ensure an even bake.","The salmon in puff pastry can be made ahead of time and frozen uncooked. Use within <b>2 weeks.<b>","Adjust cooking time in <b>step 11<b> according to time indicated on rice packet.","This pastry log encases a classic, creamy salmon and dill filling. Served with a simple lemon-flavoured risotto, this is an impressive main course for a weekend dinner party.","For extra flavour, add <b>¼ tsp<b> cayenne pepper to the salmon filling in <b>step 4.<b>"],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","45m","6 portions"]}